               <p>I am a <rs id="t17870523-35-viclabel181" type="occupation">shoe-maker</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t17870523-35-victim410 t17870523-35-viclabel181"></join>, in <placeName id="t17870523-35-crimeloc182">Cow-lane</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t17870523-35-crimeloc182" type="placeName" value="Cow-lane"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t17870523-35-crimeloc182" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t17870523-35-off179 t17870523-35-crimeloc182"></join>; the prisoner came into my shop on the 1st of May; he wanted a pair of child's shoes; I was in the room behind the shop; I heard somebody move the steps in the shop, and he reached a pair of shoes off the shelf and put them between his legs; my man's back was turned while he was reaching the shoes he asked for, I came into the shop and asked for the shoes he took off the shelf; I sent for a constable and I saw the shoes drop from him.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17870523-35-person412">
                  SAMUEL
                   EVANS
               <interp inst="t17870523-35-person412" type="surname" value="EVANS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17870523-35-person412" type="given" value="SAMUEL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17870523-35-person412" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             sworn.</p>
               <p>The prisoner had these two pair of shoes, which we suspected he had stolen some where else; they are not the prosecutor's; I have had them ever since.</p>
               <p>PRISONER's DEFENCE.</p>
               <p>I went into the shop to buy a pair of girl's shoes; I never stole a pair of shoes in my life.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t17870523-35-verdict183" type="verdictDescription">
